Classification.Comment: This sequence change creates a premature translational stop signal (p.Cys501Valfs*4) in the FAM161A gene. It is expected to result in an absent or disrupted protein product. Loss-of-function variants in FAM161A are known to be pathogenic (PMID: 20705278, 20705279, 24651477). This variant is present in population databases (rs767414973, gnomAD 0.02%). This premature translational stop signal has been observed in individuals with retinitis pigmentosa or a retinal dystrophy (PMID: 23591405, 25097241, 26574802). ClinVar contains an entry for this variant (Variation ID: 552429). For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Pathogenic.
